The paper deals with sparse recovery algorithms, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP) communities. The use of reweighted $\ell_1$ minimization is a technique that is often used in optimization (cs.NA) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
